750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*NtZPFF8fn9zqm6eEZWkIGg.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*NtZPFF8fn9zqm6eEZWkIGg.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*NtZPFF8fn9zqm6eEZWkIGg.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*NtZPFF8fn9zqm6eEZWkIGg.png 1400w"/><img alt="" loading="lazy" role="presentation" src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:700/1*NtZPFF8fn9zqm6eEZWkIGg.png"></picture></div><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">I recently finished the <em>#100DaysOfCode</em> challenge, tracked weekly on my <a href="https://twitter.com/memopussle" target="_self">Twitter.</a> I promise my past self to write an article about my progress, achievements and learned lessons after finishing this journey. So to my past self and anyone who is in the 100 Days of Code challenge or planning to do it, this article is dedicated to you! :)</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Before starting the journey, although I had seen a lot of people getting a job right after or even during the challenge, and I had so many times daydreamed that I could after it, I didn’t expect much out of it. I started it because of the “herd phenomenon” — everyone does it, so I must do it. It sounds silly — but FOMO can push you to go forward and get out of your comfort zone! I want to be like everybody else and see how far I can achieve.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">To make it easier, I make some modifications to the original #100DaysOfCode rules- that there are no strict rules! I don’t code consecutively every day — I can take a few break days if I want. I don’t need to code any time minimum; just showing up for 5–10 minutes would do it. And there’s no strict learning path; I will learn whatever I want!</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Not being strict with myself at the beginning of the journey is crucial; I know I won’t do it if it’s too hard or if I feel peer pressured. So if you just start — Don’t be too hard on yourself! It can be challenging to create a new habit, but once you start and get the rhythm, you will naturally do it every day.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-5">I. How my #100DaysOfCode went</h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">My motivation was incredibly high when I started, but it soon went downhill after one week of learning. Most people feel the same when they start something new but lose motivation quickly when they hit a roadblock. It’s the most common reason why people quit.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">I understand that I have those days when I don’t feel like studying or having imposter syndrome. This was when I knew I couldn’t rely on motivation; I needed discipline. So during that downtime, I chose to show up for a short time, and if the theories get too complicated or I get stuck, I walk away, take a break, and try again tomorrow :) I took so many breaks in 1 day (sometimes very long breaks) until I felt good again and returned to study.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">After about one week of studying React, I started to code along with a few React tutorials and made a few projects applying what I learnt to them. The only motivation that pushed me to create projects was to apply for an internship at Summer Of Tech. If you don’t know, Summer Of Tech is a New Zealand organisation for students looking for opportunities in the tech industry. Having a goal in mind seemed to speed up my learning and make it more enjoyable. Sometimes I felt pretty stressed about balancing my learning time with my school time and quite demotivated when I had to spend a few days fixing a bug in my project. Still, overall, it was pretty challenging yet satisfying in the end.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">I then wanted to learn about AWS and what’s the hype about it. The easiest way was to obtain an AWS C01 exam — fulfilling my curiosity and make myself recognisable on Linkedin for future opportunities. I spent up to 3 weeks studying it and had many down moments while learning it due to information overload. But I passed the exam in the end! I then continued to learn more about creating a Dynamo table, a stack in my set-up environments (Infrastructure as Code) until my last day of<em> #100DaysOfCode.</em></p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-5">II. Achievements during #100DaysOfCode</h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">My achievement is nothing compared to others, but I’m proud of myself for such small wins and stick it out until the end! 🥳 In the past 100 days of coding, these are what I have learnt and achieved so far:</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
